{QC 3} The Supreme Court interprets the "arising under" jurisdiction in Article III more broadly than its statutory interpretation in 28 U.S.C. §1331 (Mottley rule).
{QC 4} Congress has not repealed the Mottley rule despite Osborn v. Bank of the United States establishing a broader interpretation of Article III's "arising under" jurisdiction.
{QC 5} Congress can grant less than the full Article III jurisdiction to federal courts.
